@page "/components/chart"

<PageTitle>Chart — Lumeo</PageTitle>

<PageHeader Title="Charts" Description="Beautiful charts built on Apache ECharts. Lumeo includes 30 chart components for every visualization need, from basic bar charts to advanced geographic maps and word clouds." />

<InstallUsage Component="Chart" Package="Lumeo.Charts" />

<Alert Variant="Alert.AlertVariant.Info" ShowIcon="true" Class="mt-6 mb-2">
    <ChildContent>
        <strong>Dependencies &amp; licensing — Apache 2.0, fully free for any use.</strong>
        Powered by <a href="https://echarts.apache.org/" class="underline hover:text-foreground">Apache ECharts</a>
        (Apache License 2.0), loaded once on demand. No commercial license, no attribution requirement beyond
        Apache 2.0's standard notice. ECharts is the same engine used by Alibaba, Baidu, and many enterprise
        BI products.
    </ChildContent>
</Alert>

<Alert Variant="Alert.AlertVariant.Warning" ShowIcon="true" Class="mb-2">
    <ChildContent>
        <strong>Privacy: ECharts loads from a CDN by default.</strong>
        On the first chart render Lumeo.Charts injects the ECharts script from
        <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">cdn.jsdelivr.net</code> &mdash; a third-party request that
        discloses the visitor's IP to the CDN, independent of any cookie consent. Under GDPR that is a data
        transfer you should disclose or avoid. To keep charts on your own origin, self-host ECharts and point the
        library's documented override at it &mdash; any one of:
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>Run <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">lumeo deps install</code> to vendor every
                CDN dependency into <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">wwwroot/lib/lumeo-vendor/</code>
                and emit a <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">window.lumeoCdn</code> map pointing at them.</li>
            <li>Set it yourself before Blazor boots:
                <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">window.lumeoCdn = &#123; echarts: '/lib/echarts.min.js' &#125;</code>.</li>
            <li>Per chart: <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;Chart EChartsSource="/lib/echarts.min.js" … /&gt;</code>.</li>
        </ul>
        This documentation site itself self-hosts a pinned ECharts 5.6.0 from its own origin, so the charts on
        this page contact no third party.
    </ChildContent>
</Alert>

